    .wheel iron
    .xmas santa
    .yacht rudder
  ]
  ;
  [ airport bike car dingy engine frog garage house iron jet knife lung
    man napkin oar plum queen rudder ship toe uterus vein wheel xmas
    yacht zipper
  ]
}
><:[module: . compute thread .timestamp 2009-04-26T18:50:46.058+02 .language system]><;
!!
@ [compute] thread: .next .compute .save

Input:
  next - an object,  next next  gets next item to compute
  compute - function to apply to items
  save - function for saving results

The  next  and  save  objects may use system calls and manipulate
the user interface directly. The  compute  function must use knots if
it needs such operations.

Output: Returns [], creates a worker thread that repeatedly
gets requests, computes them and saves the results.

Why:
Useful for parsing files and doing other lengthy computations while
staying responsive to user input.

How:
The worker thread enters a loop, using knotted calls to get
and save items.
!!

{ thread: .next .compute .save
| :ok
  :thread :exit
  [next] call (knot: next) or (exit := ())
  repeat: compute -> knot: save -> [ok: next] -> next
}
><:[module: . compute trees .timestamp 2009-04-26T18:06:01.604+02 .language system]><;
!!
@ [compute] trees

Input: a list of name-value pairs, the names being constant lists.

Output: a list of trees, grouping the paths by common beginnings.
Order is preserved when possible.

Why:
Useful for populating tree views, and for multi-level categorizing.
!!

{ trees: & items
| :try
  ( items:
    .. every
      {& = name|:ok ;name .value name}
      {ok = ;name & = ? .value?|:ok}
      .:need
      legs {n := item|:ok n: .; item}
    .prefix 0
  )
  call
  { items: ..prefix
  | :who :ok
    items groups {n: .; ;name .value?|:ok name -# prefix ++# 1}
    legs
    {(branch,) := items = (n: .; ?) 1|:ok n: .; branch: .; who items: ..prefix . + 1}
    {() := ok | :ok}
    splice order [call: n] every
    {n: .; ok|:ok}
    {n: .; ;name .value|:ok value: .}
  }
}
><:[module: . compute trees test .timestamp 2009-04-26T18:07:01.354+02 .language system]><;
{ .test
| :ok yx:
  @
  trees:
  [ Oslo Stockholm Copenhagen,
    Copenhagen Berlin Vienna Rome,
    London Paris Rome Paris London,
    Washington NewYork,
    Washington Detroit,
    Calcutta Calcutta Calcutta
  ]
  every {name|:ok ;name .value name}
}
